## Authentication

The provider needs a `username` plus either a `password` or a JWT `token`. Credentials can be set in the provider block or via environment variables:

```shell
export NAYATEL_USERNAME="your-username"
export NAYATEL_PASSWORD="your-password"
# or, instead of a password:
export NAYATEL_TOKEN="your-jwt-token"
```

-> When authenticating with a password, the obtained session token is cached under `~/.config/nayatel/` and reused until it expires, so repeated Terraform runs do not re-authenticate.

